						<summary>

						<p>This is much damaged. It is dated Śaka 1458, Durmukhi, Aṟpaśi [20]. It seems to register some endowment for the conduct of a festival in the temple in the month of Śittirai every year, by the <hi rend="italic">Nāṭṭavar</hi> of Kāṉa-nāḍu probably in conjunction with some men of the army. Mention is made of an agent of the king by name Rāśi-Mudaliyār and of one Vijayālayadēvar.</p>						

						</summary>
